Here we consider 3 types of pairwise similarities, measured by the colour difference, colour histogram difference and texture disparity in terms of local binary patterns (LBP) [33], which take the conventional form:
S(k)pq = e −γ‖s(k)p −s(k)q ‖, k = 1, 2, 3;
where s(k)p , s (k) q are the observation values of the superpixel p, q calculated from colour, colour histogram and LBP; ‖·‖ denotes the `2 norm of a vector and γ is a constant.
